menu "breadboard: bb_wifi (routes)"

config BB_WIFI_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Auto-init WiFi STA via bb_registry EARLY tier"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_wifi self-registers in the EARLY tier via
        BB_REGISTRY_REGISTER_EARLY so bb_registry_init_early() calls
        bb_wifi_init_sta() automatically. Disable if the application
        drives WiFi init manually (e.g. provisioning mode, AP mode,
        or custom retry policy).

config BB_WIFI_RETRY_FOREVER_WHEN_VALIDATED
    bool "Retry wifi forever when OTA is validated"
    default y
    depends on BB_WIFI_AUTOREGISTER
    help
      When the running firmware has been validated (bb_ota_is_validated()
      is true), bb_wifi_autoinit retries the STA connect indefinitely on
      cold-boot timeout instead of falling back to AP mode. A network
      outage shouldn't wipe credentials on a known-good build. Disable
      this if you want strict timeout-then-AP behavior even for validated
      firmware.

config BB_WIFI_ROUTES_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Auto-register /api/wifi and /api/scan HTTP routes via bb_registry"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_wifi self-registers GET /api/wifi (driver state +
        connection diagnostics) and GET /api/scan (async scan results) through
        bb_registry. The wifi driver init APIs (bb_wifi_init, _init_sta,
        _ensure_netif, etc.) stay caller-driven regardless of this flag.

config BB_WIFI_RECONFIGURE
    bool "Enable runtime wifi reconfigure + pending-creds try on boot"
    default y
    help
        Enables bb_wifi_reconfigure() which stages new credentials and reboots
        to try them. On boot, if pending creds get an IP they are committed as
        the new live credentials. On timeout the pending creds are cleared and
        the device reboots onto the prior live creds without incrementing
        boot_count. When disabled bb_wifi_reconfigure() returns BB_ERR_UNSUPPORTED
        and the autoinit path is byte-for-byte identical to the baseline.

config BB_WIFI_PENDING_TRY_TIMEOUT_S
    int "Bounded connect timeout for a runtime wifi reconfigure try (seconds)"
    default 30
    range 10 120
    depends on BB_WIFI_RECONFIGURE
    help
        Maximum time (seconds) to wait for an IP when attempting to connect
        with pending (staged) credentials. On timeout the pending creds are
        discarded, the device reboots onto the prior live credentials, and
        boot_count is NOT incremented.

config BB_WIFI_RECONN_CONNECTING_TIMEOUT_MS
    int "WiFi ST_CONNECTING watchdog timeout (ms)"
    range 5000 120000
    default 30000
    help
        If neither GOT_IP nor DISCONNECT arrives within this window after
        issuing esp_wifi_connect(), the reconnect manager treats the
        association as stalled, re-issues esp_wifi_disconnect +
        esp_wifi_connect, and stays in ST_CONNECTING. 30 s >> normal
        associate+DHCP (2–8 s), so false positives are rare.

config BB_WIFI_RECONN_PERSISTENT_FAIL_WINDOW_S
    int "WiFi persistent-fail safeguard reboot window (seconds)"
    range 60 3600
    default 300
    help
        If the device keeps failing to connect for longer than this window
        (measured from the first disconnect after boot), the reconnect
        manager triggers a safeguard reboot. Default 300 s (5 minutes)
        matches the legacy hard-coded value. On validated firmware the
        reboot does not increment boot_count.

choice BB_WIFI_POWER_SAVE
    prompt "WiFi power-save mode"
    default BB_WIFI_PS_MIN_MODEM
    help
        WiFi modem power-save. MIN_MODEM (default) sleeps the radio between
        beacons to save power but can cause beacon-miss/idle disconnects on
        quiet links; NONE keeps the radio always on for best link stability
        (recommended for mains-powered/always-on devices like miners).
    config BB_WIFI_PS_NONE
        bool "None (radio always on)"
    config BB_WIFI_PS_MIN_MODEM
        bool "Minimum modem sleep"
    config BB_WIFI_PS_MAX_MODEM
        bool "Maximum modem sleep"
endchoice

config BB_WIFI_NO_IP_WATCHDOG_ENABLE
    bool "Enable no-IP watchdog (mode-a) and inactive-time zombie recovery (mode-b)"
    default n
    help
        Enable mode-a no-IP watchdog + mode-b inactive-time zombie recovery.
        When disabled, ST_IDLE uses portMAX_DELAY (no periodic check) and
        inactive-time is not configured.

config BB_WIFI_NO_IP_WATCHDOG_S
    int "No-IP watchdog interval for ST_IDLE (seconds)"
    range 10 600
    default 60
    depends on BB_WIFI_NO_IP_WATCHDOG_ENABLE
    help
        When the reconnect manager is in ST_IDLE (connected, not reconnecting),
        this is the interval at which it checks whether the board is still L2-
        associated but has lost its DHCP IP (zombie state). On detection it calls
        bb_wifi_restart_sta() to drop the stale association and trigger recovery.
        60 s is the default — long enough to avoid false positives from DHCP
        renewal races, short enough to recover quickly from a genuine zombie.

config BB_WIFI_INACTIVE_TIME_S
    int "Inactive time for beacon-loss detection (seconds)"
    range 3 600
    default 45
    depends on BB_WIFI_NO_IP_WATCHDOG_ENABLE
    help
        Configures the WiFi driver's inactive time via esp_wifi_set_inactive_time().
        If the station receives no beacon from the AP within this window, the driver
        emits WIFI_EVENT_STA_DISCONNECTED, which the reconnect FSM handles normally.
        Minimum 3 (ESP-IDF hard floor). 45 s gives enough margin above power-save
        beacon intervals while detecting stuck egress faster than the default 6 s.

config BB_WIFI_EGRESS_PROBE_S
    int "Egress probe interval for ST_IDLE (seconds)"
    range 5 600
    default 30
    depends on BB_WIFI_NO_IP_WATCHDOG_ENABLE
    help
        When the reconnect manager is in ST_IDLE (connected, IP present),
        this is the interval at which it pings the default gateway to detect
        egress-dead zombie state (mode-b: board has IP+association but no
        real egress). On N consecutive failures (BB_WIFI_EGRESS_PROBE_FAILS)
        it calls bb_wifi_restart_sta() to recover. 30 s is a good default —
        fast enough to detect egress death within ~90 s, slow enough to avoid
        ICMP noise on a congested AP.

config BB_WIFI_EGRESS_PROBE_FAILS
    int "Consecutive egress probe failures before recovery"
    range 1 20
    default 3
    depends on BB_WIFI_NO_IP_WATCHDOG_ENABLE
    help
        Number of consecutive failed gateway pings before the egress-dead
        recovery path calls bb_wifi_restart_sta(). At the default 30 s probe
        interval, 3 failures = ~90 s to declare egress dead. Lower for
        faster reaction, higher to tolerate transient ICMP drops.

endmenu
